# 📌 Mongoose CRUD Operations (Node.js + MongoDB)

This project demonstrates **CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete)** operations using **Node.js, MongoDB, and Mongoose**.
It is a beginner-friendly implementation to understand how Mongoose interacts with MongoDB.

---

## 🚀 Features

* ➕ Create single and multiple users
* 📖 Read all users and specific users
* 🔍 Find by ID and conditions
* ✏️ Update user data
* 🗑️ Delete single and multiple users
* ⚡ Uses Mongoose schema & model

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

* **Backend:** Node.js
* **Database:** MongoDB
* **ODM:** Mongoose

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```id="r1n3xq"
project/
│── index.js       # Main file (all CRUD operations)
│── package.json
```

---

## ⚙️ Installation & Setup

1. Clone the repository

```id="5f1l2p"
git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo-name.git
```

2. Navigate to project folder

```id="q8d2mz"
cd your-repo-name
```

3. Install dependencies

```id="2df9xt"
npm install
```

4. Start MongoDB locally
   Make sure MongoDB is running on:

```id="m3k7dp"
mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/test
```

5. Run the project

```id="c7p4k9"
node index.js
```

---

## 📊 CRUD Operations Covered

### ➕ Create

* `new User().save()`
* `User.insertMany()`

### 📖 Read

* `User.find()`
* `User.findOne()`
* `User.findById()`

### ✏️ Update

* `User.updateOne()`
* `User.findOneAndUpdate()`
* `User.findByIdAndUpdate()`

### 🗑️ Delete

* `User.deleteOne()`
* `User.deleteMany()`
* `User.findByIdAndDelete()`
* `User.findOneAndDelete()`

---

## 🧠 Learning Outcome

* Understanding of **MongoDB collections & documents**
* How **Mongoose schema and models** work
* Performing real-world **database operations in Node.js**
* Difference between update methods and delete methods

